The article discusses the recent verdict in the case of Kate Steinle, who was killed by an illegal immigrant and convicted felon in San Francisco. The article emphasizes the danger to public safety when the country fails to enforce its laws and highlights the fact that the perpetrator had been deported five times. It calls for Congress to secure the borders, provide resources to deport criminal illegal immigrants, and put an end to sanctuary city policies. The article holds politicians accountable for preventable crimes committed against innocent Americans and suggests that if San Francisco had enforced immigration laws, the Steinle family would not have suffered this loss.